description: The lockdown will continue until at least 5 May, Taoiseach Leo Varadkar announces.
title: Coronavirus: Irish restrictions extended until 5 May
title_page: Coronavirus: Irish restrictions extended until 5 May - BBC News
maintext: While the lifting of any restrictions would be gradual, they would not happen until there was more confidence the virus would not spread further. If it did, restrictions would need to be re-introduced.
